Casual Gamers are the exception , not the norm in high end guilds.   You cant survive on casual gamers , you need hardcore players that make 90% of the raids to be really succesful or else the hardcore will become frustrated to be working hard for the guild and seeing the other sonly log in on saturdays .   They will then leave and try to find a guild with players who play the game the same way they do.<br>
<br>
You wont do much if your 5 clerics all log in on different days of the week.  <br>
<br>
Also it depends on how you define a Succesful Guild .  If it raiding high-end content , then hardcore players will be mostly responsible for your succes because without them there would be like 1 raid a week and those craving raid would leave.   <br>
<br>
Also a strong and fair guild leader will have a big impact on the succes of a guild.  Some people seem to be made to be guild leader , it comes naturally to them.<br>
