What makes a guild successful?<br>
<br>
Finding good people behind the characters who know how to play their class. Not just clicking heal buttons, but people who strive to better themselves at their class. <br>
<br>
Finding people who want to focus on achieving things before loot interests. Sure, boss mob X has $$$ loot, but just remind yourself that you'll get it eventually and /grats whoever gets it before you if they do. <br>
<br>
Finding people that patient and loyal. Not people that join your guild to get their epics and then 2 weeks later leave to join the 'uber' guild with barely a thank you. <br>
<br>
Finding good people to take the lead as officers in such a way that others will listen to them and they get things done. These are the people who talk/listen and research mobs, strats, info, etc to make raids successful or at least they learn and adapt in order to get better each time. A good officer is something very special to a Guildleader and their efforts are appreciated.<br>
<br>
Avoid recruiting 10 clerics just cuz they're clerics. Same for any needed class. Find SKILLED people. Just cuz you have a high amount of clerics, rogues, warriors, wizards, etc doesn't mean a thing if they are idiots. 30 very competant people can do the job of 50 morons almost every time. <br>
<br>
People should have a friendship with their guilders inorder to create that bond to where people dont want to leave. Help others with quests, XP groups, epics, etc. Think about the people who you'd drop everything to help - why is that? Cuz those are the ones who have done the same for you. <br>
<br>
Avoid growing too fast in an effort to compete with guildX or guildZ. Keep things going steady and they'll progress. But if you're trying to create a guild of lvl 40-50ish people, there needs to be split time for raids and XPing and Epics. But if it's more for 55-60 levels, then do what you can to keep people busy. Schedule raids appropiate to you guild's abilities but also others to at least attempt so people can strive for goals. <br>
<br>
Don't strive to be the next CC or PO or anyone. Strive to be the best your guild can be. Many of us can remember when Fire Giants was a guild raid, or Phinny ) <br>
<br>
Enjoy the game. Sometimes that's easier said than done, but it's the purpose of it all. <br>
<br>
/shrugs   just some thots I had to the question, hope it helps<br>
<br>
