<br>
Just depends on the person really. I agree with Tuvan about the things that make a guild a good thing but the reasons he listed are more something an individual would consider, whether the guild is right for them etc. I guess if everyone in a guild can answer yes to Tuvan's questions then its a success but I don't imagine such a guild exists most of the time as a single event can totally change a persons opinion of things.<br>
<br>
I doubt there's any true formula for determining guild success but I think what Tuvan posted is what it pretty much boils down to after all a guild is made of nothing if not individuals.<br>
<br>
Some people see others in this game merely as slightly more intelligent NPCs who are there to see them achieve their goals, others are in it for the family thing. Either way its up to everyone to judge whether they think their guild is a success and choose whether to fight to make it better or to bail on their friends.<br>
<br>
