p.s. plus drugs <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ubigemnoseandhow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>bigemnose andhow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 98<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/4/02 11:54:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3322.topic&index=13>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> There is no simple answer</span><hr size=1> I hate to say it, but there is no simple answer.<br>
<br>
There just is no simple answer because what makes a successful guild successful is completely dependent on what you define 'a successful guild' as being.<br>
<br>
My guild was formed little over a month ago, and I consider it successful.  That being said, others likely will disagree.  For instance, when I created my guild a month+ ago, I left a guild that was doing semi-high end content (not uber content, but getting close).  The guild I formed does low end content like Kaesora on alts for fun.  We have about 20 members, and we all play at our leasure which means that we oftenly are not all on at the same time.  To most people that play EQ, this is a very UNSUCCESSFUL guild.  But, to me and my members, this is one of the more SUCCESSFUL guilds that we have ever been in.  We just enjoy the game for what it is... entertainment.<br>
<br>
So basically, what I am trying to say is that you need to make the decission on what success means to your guild if you are the leader.  Those people that leave your guild because of what you define as the goal of your guild were not meant to be there.  There is nothing wrong with those individuals moving on.  It will take time, but eventually you will get the kinds of people in your guild that like your goals, and then you will really start to enjoy the game.<br>
<br>
Have fun.<br>
