<br>
In any case, if I were to offer some suggestions for what makes a successful guild I would have to include:<br>
<br>
1. people who log on everyday for at least 5+ hours a day<br>
<br>
2. lots and lots of skilled clerics<br>
<br>
3. a good puller who isn't reliant on ShowEQ<br>
<br>
4. selflessness where loot and fellow guildmembers are concerned. <br>
<br>
5. a capable leader who logs on regularly and knows what is going on within the guild interpersonally.<br>
<br>
6. active witty banter in guild chat. or disgusting vile suggestions and innuendos. Either works wonders for morale.<br>
<br>
There are probably more but these 6 are the fundamentals, I would venture. <p>Prybutok Agonista<br>
